claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A table summarizing demographic and clinical characteristics (sex, race/ethnicity, coexisting illnesses, and prior-year flu vaccination) of participants who received a recombinant vaccine versus a standard-dose vaccine. The table provides only participant demographics and clinical history; it contains no information on antigenic matching or WHO/FDA strain selection, and therefore does not support the claim.
